Software requirements?
======================

  On all Perl-Platforms! You need:
    * min. Perl5
    * Database (e. g. MySQL, PostgreSQL)
    * Webpserver (mod_perl isn't required but very nice to have)
    * some CPAN-Module (CGI, MIME::Words, Mail::Internet, MIME::Parser, DBI,
      DBD::mysql) and for stats (GD, GD::Graph, GD::Graph::lines, Date::Calc)

Instalation:
============

1. Install CPAN Modules (if needed):
   perl -MCPAN -e shell;
   ...
   install MIME::Words
   install MIME::Parser
   ...

2. create user and install tar.gz 

   $shell: mkdir /opt/OpenTRS/
   $shell: useradd -d /opt/OpenTRS/ otrs
   $shell: cd /opt/OpenTRS/
   $shell: tar -xzvf OpenTRS-xxxx-xx-xx.tar-gz
   $shell: chown -r /opt/OpenTRS/* otrs
   
3. Database:
   rcmysql start
   cat install/mysql/db_create.sql  | mysql -u root

4. Webserver:
   Configfile /etc/httpd/httpd.conf
   [...]
   User OpenTRS-User
   [...]
   ScriptAlias /cgi-bin/ "/opt/OpenTRS/bin/cgi-bin/"
   [...]
   <IfDefine PERL>
   Alias /otrs/ "/opt/OpenTRS/bin/cgi-bin/"
   </IfDefine>
   <Location /otrs>
   SetHandler  perl-script
   PerlHandler Apache::PerlRun
   Options ExecCGI
   PerlSendHeader On
   </Location>

5. Config file ($HOME/Kernel/Config.pm):
   Set some Kernel::Config Options

6. First Login:
   http://host/cgi-bin/index.pl
   User: root@localhost
   PW: root

   --> goto AdminArea and set some config setings.

7. First Email:
   use the procmailrc of the OpenTRS-User --> /opt/OpenTRS/.procmailrc

8.  First Email:
   use the procmailrc of the OpenTRS_User --> /opt/OpenTRS/.procmailrc

   or pipe a email direct into $OpenTRS_HOME/bin/Postmaster.pl
    (e. g. 'cat /tmp/email | $OpenTRS_HOME/bin/Postmaster.pl').

Have a lot of fun.

 Martin Edenhofer 

(December 2001 Frankfurt/Germany)

